The paper focuses on online social networks and the psychological determinants of online social dynamics. It analyzes users' behavior on Facebook pages and their personality traits, which suggests that it could fall under the categories of social networks (cs.SOC), cyber security (cs.CYBER), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, the paper's main focus is on the classification of personality traits, which makes social computing (cs.SI) the most likely category.
